Phase 3 – DNS Administration and Record Management

Objective

Configure and validate DNS records within the Active Directory environment by creating A records, CNAME aliases, and testing name resolution.

Tasks Completed

* Accessed and managed the Active Directory DNS Forward Lookup Zone.
* Created an A record to map a hostname (`fileserver`) to the server IP address.
* Created a CNAME record (`storage`) as an alias pointing to `fileserver.home.lab`.
* Verified DNS resolution using `nslookup`.
* Confirmed successful hostname-to-IP address resolution within the domain environment.

Skills Demonstrated

* Windows Server DNS Administration
* DNS Forward Lookup Zones
* A Record Configuration
* CNAME Record Configuration
* DNS Name Resolution
* `nslookup` Troubleshooting
* Active Directory Integrated DNS
* Basic Network Troubleshooting
